PHP South Africa will happen from 26 to 28 September at Blandford Manor in Randburg. This is the fifth annual PHP South Africa, with the organisers promising the biggest conference yet. “It’s literally a conference by developers, for developers in the hopes to upskill all South Africans and grow the community,” the organisers told MyBroadband. “From this we have started meetups in Cape Town, Johannesburg, and Pretoria. It’s becoming a great success, and we’ve had a lot of positive feedback.” PHP South Africa will run from 09:00 every day. The first day will feature two workshop sessions, while 27 and 28 September will be conference days. Tickets are available through the conference website, and are priced as follows: